The article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring April 12, 2016, as National Equal Pay Day. The proclamation highlights the issue of gender pay gap in the United States and emphasizes the importance of equal pay for equal work. It mentions that women in the U.S. earn only 79 cents for every dollar earned by men, with women of color facing even greater disparities. The proclamation calls for action to address pay discrimination, pay secrecy, pregnancy discrimination, and unconscious bias. It mentions the efforts made by the Obama administration, such as the proposal to gather pay data by race, ethnicity, and gender, and the call for Congress to pass the Paycheck Fairness Act. The proclamation concludes by urging Americans to recognize the value of women's skills and contributions, acknowledge wage inequality, and work towards achieving equal pay.